50|$|Pöytäpaska (Table Shit) {{also known}} as Espanjalainen paskahousu (Spanish Shitpants) can be played by two or three players. The rules {{are the same as}} in Paskahousu, with the {{following}} additions. In addition to the hand, each player is dealt four cards face down and four cards face up on the table. They are played after the stock and the <b>cards</b> in your <b>hand</b> have exhausted. The cards face up are played before the cards face down. Note that you are allowed to see a face down card only when you (try to) play it. If it cannot be played according to the rules, you must take the card and the entire pile to your hand. If you must take the pile when playing the table cards, the pile becomes your <b>hand</b> <b>cards,</b> and you must get rid of your <b>hand</b> <b>cards</b> before you can continue playing from the table.|$|R
